<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Visualization on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/visualization/</link><description>Recent content in Visualization on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/visualization/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Linux grafana Dashboard Error — Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-grafana-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-grafana-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-grafana-dashboard-error"&gt;Linux: grafana: dashboard error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;grafana: dashboard error&lt;/code&gt; message means Grafana encountered a problem loading, rendering, or querying a dashboard. This can appear as blank panels, &amp;ldquo;No data&amp;rdquo; messages, datasource connection failures, or dashboard JSON errors. The error typically indicates a problem with the datasource, query, or Grafana configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Grafana dashboards contain panels that query datasources (Prometheus, Elasticsearch, InfluxDB, etc.). When a dashboard fails, it&amp;rsquo;s usually because: the datasource is unreachable, the query has syntax errors, the dashboard JSON is corrupted, or Grafana&amp;rsquo;s backend services are not functioning properly.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ImportError: matplotlib not found — ModuleNotFoundError Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/importerror-matplotlib/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/importerror-matplotlib/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="importerror-matplotlib-not-found--modulenotfounderror-fix"&gt;ImportError: matplotlib not found — ModuleNotFoundError Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;ImportError: matplotlib not found&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'matplotlib'&lt;/code&gt; means Python cannot locate the matplotlib package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;matplotlib is a plotting library. It is not part of the standard library and must be installed separately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: matplotlib not installed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; matplotlib &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ModuleNotFoundError: No module named &amp;#39;matplotlib&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Installed for wrong Python version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-install-with-pip"&gt;Fix 1: Install with pip&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install matplotlib
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# For a specific version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install matplotlib&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;3.8.2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-install-in-the-correct-virtual-environment"&gt;Fix 2: Install in the correct virtual environment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source venv/bin/activate
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install matplotlib
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;python -c &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;import matplotlib; print(matplotlib.__version__)&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-plotly/ — ImportError: plotly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-seaborn/ — ImportError: seaborn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-numpy/ — ImportError: numpy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ImportError: plotly not found — ModuleNotFoundError Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/importerror-plotly/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/importerror-plotly/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="importerror-plotly-not-found--modulenotfounderror-fix"&gt;ImportError: plotly not found — ModuleNotFoundError Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;ImportError: plotly not found&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'plotly'&lt;/code&gt; means Python cannot locate the plotly package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;plotly is an interactive graphing library. It is not part of the standard library and must be installed separately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: plotly not installed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; plotly &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ModuleNotFoundError: No module named &amp;#39;plotly&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Installed for wrong Python version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-install-with-pip"&gt;Fix 1: Install with pip&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install plotly
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# With optional dependencies&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install plotly&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;express&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-install-in-the-correct-virtual-environment"&gt;Fix 2: Install in the correct virtual environment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source venv/bin/activate
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install plotly
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;python -c &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;import plotly; print(plotly.__version__)&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-matplotlib/ — ImportError: matplotlib&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-seaborn/ — ImportError: seaborn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-pandas/ — ImportError: pandas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ImportError: seaborn not found — ModuleNotFoundError Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/importerror-seaborn/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/importerror-seaborn/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="importerror-seaborn-not-found--modulenotfounderror-fix"&gt;ImportError: seaborn not found — ModuleNotFoundError Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;ImportError: seaborn not found&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'seaborn'&lt;/code&gt; means Python cannot locate the seaborn package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;seaborn is a statistical data visualization library built on matplotlib. It is not part of the standard library and must be installed separately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: seaborn not installed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; seaborn &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ModuleNotFoundError: No module named &amp;#39;seaborn&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Installed for wrong Python version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-install-with-pip"&gt;Fix 1: Install with pip&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install seaborn
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-install-in-the-correct-virtual-environment"&gt;Fix 2: Install in the correct virtual environment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source venv/bin/activate
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install seaborn
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;python -c &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;import seaborn; print(seaborn.__version__)&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-matplotlib/ — ImportError: matplotlib&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-pandas/ — ImportError: pandas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/languages/python/importerror-numpy/ — ImportError: numpy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] R Error — Error in Plot Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/r/error-in-plot/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/r/error-in-plot/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="error-in-plot--fix"&gt;Error in Plot — Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;Error in plot(...) : invalid input type&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;plot.new() has not been called&lt;/code&gt; occurs when &lt;code&gt;plot()&lt;/code&gt; receives invalid data or when plotting functions are called out of order.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-r" data-lang="r"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: Non-numeric data&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;plot&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;b&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;c&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Error: invalid input type&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Mismatched x and y lengths&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;plot&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Error: &amp;#39;x&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;y&amp;#39; lengths differ&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Calling points() before plot()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;points&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Error: plot.new() has not been called&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 4: Complex data in simple plot&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;plot&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2i&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Error: invalid input type&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-ensure-numeric-data"&gt;Fix 1: Ensure numeric data&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-r" data-lang="r"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;plot&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;b&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;c&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;plot&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-match-x-and-y-lengths"&gt;Fix 2: Match x and y lengths&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-r" data-lang="r"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;plot&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;y &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;7&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;9&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;plot&lt;/span&gt;(x, y)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-call-plot-before-points"&gt;Fix 3: Call plot() before points()&lt;/h3&gt;
